lyrics:
Some people have long missed the sea
In the past, the sea was blue, unlike now the sea is deserted
My words are small, the wind screams high, the sea is filled with pain
Your love is so great that the waves will break and my life will be lost
The dream of no longer having the sea has dried up
Without you in this world, the sea silently mourns with me
With me the sea dies, with you the sea dissolves
Thousands of years of pain turn into clouds, thousand years of loneliness and dry seas
